有1个儿子。他去世于1340年在英国哈普爾易斯爾 本 懷特享年29岁。"},"hr":{"about 1312–1340":"oko 1312.–1340.","1312–1340":"1312–1340.","1315–Female":"1315–preminula","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1285–1340":"1285–1340.","1290–Female":"1290–preminula","1340":"1340.","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1312":"1312","1453":"1453","about 1312":"oko 1312.","about 1335":"oko 1335.","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1438":"1438","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, England","Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England":"Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England","North Cadbury, Somerset, England":"North Cadbury, Somerset, England"},"cs":{"about 1312–1340":"okolo 1312–1340","1312–1340":"1312–1340","1315–Female":"1315–Zesnulá","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1285–1340":"1285–1340","1290–Female":"1290–Zesnulá","1340":"1340","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1312":"1312","1453":"1453","about 1312":"okolo 1312","about 1335":"okolo 1335","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1438":"1438","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, Anglie","Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England":"Isle of Wight, Hampshire, Anglie","North Cadbury, Somerset, England":"North Cadbury, Somerset, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1312–1340":"omkring 1312–1340","1312–1340":"1312–1340","1315–Female":"1315–Afdød","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1285–1340":"1285–1340","1290–Female":"1290–Afdød","1340":"1340","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1312":"1312","1453":"1453","about 1312":"omkring 1312","about 1335":"omkring 1335","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1438":"1438","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, England","Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England":"Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England","North Cadbury, Somerset, England":"North Cadbury, Somerset, England"},"nl":{"about 1312–1340":"circa 1312–1340","1312–1340":"1312–1340","1315–Female":"1315–Overleden","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1285–1340":"1285–1340","1290–Female":"1290–Overleden","1340":"1340","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1312":"1312","1453":"1453","about 1312":"circa 1312","about 1335":"circa 1335","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1438":"1438","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, England","Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England":"Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England","North Cadbury, Somerset, England":"North Cadbury, Somerset, England"},"en":{"about 1312–1340":"about 1312–1340","1312–1340":"1312–1340","1315–Female":"1315–Deceased","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1285–1340":"1285–1340","1290–Female":"1290–Deceased","1340":"1340","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1312":"1312","1453":"1453","about 1312":"about 1312","about 1335":"about 1335","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1438":"1438","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, England","Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England":"Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England","North Cadbury, Somerset, England":"North Cadbury, Somerset, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Russell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish: of Norman origin, from Old French and Anglo-Norman French <i>r(o)ussel</i>, a diminutive of Old French <i>rous(e)</i> ‘red, reddish’, used either as a nickname for someone with red hair or a ruddy complexion, or as a personal name. Compare   Rouse  . This Norman name has been established in Ireland since the 12th century. It has been reinforced in Britain and Ireland by Huguenot bearers of the name <i>Roussel</i>, of the same Old French origin.","English: habitational name from any of several places called Rushall (Norfolk, Staffordshire, Wiltshire) or possibly sometimes from Rusthall in Speldhurst (Kent). Rushall in Staffordshire derives from Old English <i>rysc</i> ‘rush, rushes’ + <i>halh</i> ‘nook, corner of land’. Rushall in Norfolk derives from an uncertain first element + Old English <i>halh</i>. Rushall in Wiltshire derives from an Old English personal name <i>Rust</i> (genitive <i>Rustes</i>) + <i>halh</i>. Rusthall in Speldhurst (Kent) probably derives from Old English <i>rust</i> ‘rust, rust color’ + <i>wella</i> ‘well, spring, stream’, but with a change in the final element due to influence from Middle English, Old English <i>hall</i> ‘hall, residence’, perhaps referring to a nearby building.","Americanized form of German <b>Rüssel</b>, from a pet form of any of various personal names formed with the element <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame, renown’."],"variants":[{"name":"Russler","meanings":["German (<b>Rüssler</b>):","occupational name for a farmer, from an agent derivative of <i>rüsseln</i> ‘to shallow plow’.","variant of <b>Rüssel</b> (see   Russell   2)."]},{"name":"Rouse","meanings":["English: nickname for a person with red hair or a ruddy complexion, from Middle English, Anglo-Norman French <i>rous(e)</i> ‘red(-haired)’ (from Latin <i>russ(e)us</i>).","Americanized form of German   Raus  .","Walloon and northern French (<b>Rousé</b>): variant of <b>Rosé</b> (see   Rose  )."]},{"name":"Russel","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Russell  .","German: from a pet form of <i>Russ</i>, see   Russ   2.","northwest German (<b>Rüssel</b>): probably a variant of   Rossel  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":3,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":16,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":25,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Russell was born about 1312, his father, Sir Theobald Russell, was 29 and his mother, Eleanor de la Tour, was 24. He had at least 1 son with heiress of Muschamp. He died in 1340, in Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England, at the age of 29."},"et":{"about 1312–1340":"umbes 1312–1340","1312–1340":"1312–1340","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1335–1438":"1335–1438","1285–1340":"1285–1340","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1340":"1340","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1312":"1312","1453":"1453","about 1312":"umbes 1312","about 1335":"umbes 1335","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1438":"1438","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, England","Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England":"Isle of Wight, Hampshire, England","North Cadbury, Somerset, England":"North Cadbury, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"about 1312–134